The paper deals with user scheduling in multiuser MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of subspace analysis and angular-based criteria suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.SI) and linear algebra (cs.LG). Finally, the consideration of heterogeneous users implies a potential connection to multimedia systems (cs.MM).
